latestPosts.caption:
So I was in Lucknow for a quick minute to celebrate a close friend’s roka with a magical Sufi night and my heart is just so full 💓

Kicked things off with the mandatory airport fit check (because obv 😇), snagged a window seat for those dreamy sky views ☁️ and finally finished The Magic Shop (a book I’d paused midway). And what a read. Just the kind of magic I needed ✨

As soon as we landed, we headed straight to an intimate lunch that felt like a warm hug. Wore this gorgeous breezy printed dress from an Indian designer whose work I absolutely adore.
Look details:
Dress @siddharthabansal_
Flats @gulraj.in 
Jewels @ananaofficial

Later that evening, we got all dressed up for the most magical Sufi night, full of music, love and the kind of energy you just want to bottle up forever.
Look details:
Outfit @poojapranayofficial 
Heels @venussteps 
Bag @houseofbio_by_rittikhanna 
Jewels @ananaofficial 

And of course, before flying back, chikankari shopping was a must.

Short, sweet and filled with memories I’m keeping close.💛💫🤗
